*                 FILE: DS_CABLE.SIZ
*
* Automotive Springs Diagonal Brace Inventory
*      Cable bracing may be either cable, rods or angles. 
*
*
**************************************************************************
**     REVISED ON MAY 17, 2011 BY CDL
**************************************************************************
*
*   DESCRIPTION OF COLUMN HEADINGS:
*    - Enter cable type, diameter, and weight.
*    - Allowable tension is for wind load.
*    - Cable Offset = Distance from attachment point to end of cable 
*          loop. It is the sum for both ends.
*    - Cable Lap = Distance from end of cable loop to end of cable.
*          It is the sum of the lap for both ends.
*    - Bolt Extension = Distance from attachment point to end of bolt.
*          It is the sum of the bolt extension for both ends.
*    - Cable bracing consists of a cable plus hardware at each end.
*          Enter the cable part number and the hardware weigth and
*          part number.
*
********************************************************************************
*
*  - Capacities for ASD Design under the marker '@@CODE_WS' are with 
*    33% increase for wind load. For codes which do not allow this 33% increase
*    program will automaticaly reduce the capacities in design files
*
*  - Capacities for LRFD Design under the marker '@@CODE_LS' are without any increase
*    for wind and hence same values will be considered in design
*
********************************************************************************
*
*
*   FORMULAS FOR BILL OF MATERIALS OUTPUT:
*    - Cable length(labeled length in BOM) = Diagonal distance between
*          webs - cable offset + cable lap + bolt extension.
*    - Fabricated Length = Diagonal distance between webs + bolt extension.
*
*
* ============================================================================
**.......Rods.......  Tension  ....Rods.......  Bolt          ....Hardware.....   --Slot Size--
**Type  Diam,   Wt     Allow   Offset  Lap   Ext.             Weight,            Width   Length
**C/R/A  mm     kg/m    KN     mm      mm     mm     Part       Kg      Part       mm      mm 
**----  -----  ------ -------- ------ -----  ----- ---------- ------ ----------  ------  -------
